## Key Design Decisions

| Concern | Approach |
|---|---|
| **Access control** | Tests verify `PermissionError` for non-admin roles and `None` users before any business logic runs |
| **PII redaction** | Each PII field (`name`, `email`, `phone`) has its own test; a separate test checks that raw values don't appear anywhere in the CSV body |
| **Non-PII preservation** | Explicitly asserts `department`, `title`, `location` are intact for opted-out employees |
| **Rate limiting** | Mocked limiter; parametrised test drives the counter from 1 → limit → limit+1 across multiple quota sizes |
| **Per-user isolation** | `side_effect` lambda blocks only user A while user B succeeds in the same service instance |
| **Audit logging** | Patched at the module level; asserts `user_id`, `action`, and a timestamp range |
| **CSV validity** | Uses stdlib `csv.DictReader` to parse the output, so any structural breakage surfaces immediately |

